message.content:
A cocker spaniel is a dog breed that originated in England and was historically trained to hunt small game. 

These dogs have long, floppy ears and a silky, wavy coat that can come in a variety of colors such as black, brown, tan, and white. 

They typically have a sturdy, compact body and a friendly expression with round, dark eyes. 

Their front legs are straight and their hind legs are angled, which helps them to move quickly and nimbly. 

Cocker spaniels are typically kept as pets or used as show dogs, due to their affectionate and loyal nature, as well as their striking appearance. 

They are also commonly used as therapy dogs, due to their gentle and calming demeanor. 

Cocker spaniels can be found in homes all over the world, and are known for their loving and playful personalities.
